<p>Then I realised that if I wanted to make some short sequence out ouf it, I needed to plan for it. So with my friend Alexandre Thery we went to draw a storyboard :
at that point there was no going back</p>

<figure>
  <center>
    <img src="https://cdnb.artstation.com/p/assets/images/images/032/223/733/large/jules-mabon-img-20200530-235351.jpg?1605808731" style="width:100%" />
    </center>
</figure>

<p>With the camera moves planned we could proceed to film those people on green screens. At that point I did not have the whole scene properly modeled because we knew that we would made some unexpected change during filming. Waiting for the proper moment to meet I also prepared some props for the shoot, a gyoza box and a bipper-phone-future-thing :</p>

